 They said that they are pleased with the progress made in locating the bodies of their loved ones, but that the search was conducted out of private pockets with no help from the South African Ambassador, Mandisu Mphahlawa. They have thanked the Limpopo Premier and the Elias Motsoaledi Municipality for their support. They Mayor traveled to Mozambique to support the families. The families asked for space to grieve and continue the search for the remaining body. They said that they will not be giving personal media interviews. The body of a male was recovered on Thursday whilst the bodies of two females were recovered on Friday (yesterday).   Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za